Phase 2 Goal
Convert your Phase 1 Terraform code into a professional structure with:
	• variables
	• terraform.tfvars
	• reusable code
	• environment support

What We Will Improve
Right now your code has hardcoded values like:

cidr_block = "10.0.0.0/16"
availability_zone = "ap-south-1a"
This is not good for real projects.
Instead we will use variables.
Example:

cidr_block = var.vpc_cidr

Phase 2 Folder Structure
Inside your project:

devops-end-to-end-project
│
├ terraform
│   ├ main.tf
│   ├ provider.tf
│   ├ variables.tf
│   ├ terraform.tfvars
│   └ outputs.tf
│
├ docker
├ kubernetes
└ monitoring

Step 1 — Create variables.tf
Inside terraform folder

touch variables.tf
Add:

variable "region" {
  description = "AWS region"
  default     = "ap-south-1"
}

variable "vpc_cidr" {
  description = "VPC CIDR block"
}

variable "public_subnet_cidr" {
  description = "Public subnet CIDR"
}

variable "private_subnet_cidr" {
  description = "Private subnet CIDR"
}

variable "availability_zone" {
  description = "Availability zone"
}

Step 2 — Update provider.tf
Change provider:

provider "aws" {
  region = var.region
}
Now region is dynamic.

Step 3 — Update main.tf
Replace hardcoded values.
VPC

resource "aws_vpc" "main" {
  cidr_block = var.vpc_cidr

  tags = {
    Name = "devops-vpc"
  }
}

Public Subnet

resource "aws_subnet" "public_subnet" {
  vpc_id                  = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block              = var.public_subnet_cidr
  availability_zone       = var.availability_zone
  map_public_ip_on_launch = true

  tags = {
    Name = "public-subnet"
  }
}

Private Subnet

resource "aws_subnet" "private_subnet" {
  vpc_id            = aws_vpc.main.id
  cidr_block        = var.private_subnet_cidr
  availability_zone = var.availability_zone

  tags = {
    Name = "private-subnet"
  }
}
Everything else in your main.tf remains same.

Step 4 — Create terraform.tfvars
This file stores actual values.
Create file:

touch terraform.tfvars
Add:

region              = "ap-south-1"
vpc_cidr            = "10.0.0.0/16"
public_subnet_cidr  = "10.0.1.0/24"
private_subnet_cidr = "10.0.2.0/24"
availability_zone   = "ap-south-1a"

Step 5 — (Optional but Professional) Create outputs.tf

touch outputs.tf
Add:

output "vpc_id" {
  value = aws_vpc.main.id
}

output "public_subnet_id" {
  value = aws_subnet.public_subnet.id
}

output "private_subnet_id" {
  value = aws_subnet.private_subnet.id
}
Outputs help other Terraform modules use these resources.

Step 6 — Run Terraform
Run:

terraform init
Then:

terraform plan
Then:

terraform apply

